.TH "rb_update_event" 9 "rb_update_event" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rb_update_event \- update event type and data
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" rb_update_event
.BI "(struct ring_buffer_per_cpu *cpu_buffer "  ","
.BI "struct ring_buffer_event *event "  ","
.BI "struct rb_event_info *info "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cpu_buffer" 12
The per cpu buffer of the \fIevent\fP
.IP "event" 12
the event to update
.IP "info" 12
The info to update the \fIevent\fP with (contains length and delta)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Update the type and data fields of the \fIevent\fP. The length
is the actual size that is written to the ring buffer,
and with this, we can determine what to place into the
data field.
